<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-04T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-04T10:00:00-05:00" n="595" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/7423:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-04T17:00:00+02:00">January 4, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received January 4—4:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>21. At the Foreign Office press conference today in reply to a
                                question as to the effect of the sending of German air forces to
                                Italy it was stated that while naturally no statement could be given
                                out on purely military matters “there was no change in formal
                                German-Greek relations”.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>